法規內容.條文內容:
Training curricula that nursing personnel of health institutions implementing immunization work shall accept are as follows:
1. at least six hours of basic education and training courses in studies of vaccines, immunization practice, emergency rescue and others;
2. at least four hours every two years regularly of advanced education and training in the courses mentioned in the preceding Subparagraph;
3. for the basic and advanced education and training, certificate of credit hours shall be obtained.
Nursing personnel of the preceding Paragraph implementing immunization, their work shall include procedures such as health and adequacy assessment before implementation of immunization, accessing vaccines, immunization preparedness, verification of vaccines, confirmation of immunization targets, vaccine administration, and health education; they shall implement immunization work only in the following places:
1. competent health authorities and their affiliated health stations (rooms), schools at various levels;
2. registered nursing homes, care and nursing care institutions for the elderly;
3. other places approved by the central competent health authority.

New enrollees of primary schools and educational institutions shall, upon enrolment, submit for examination immunization records that meet the schedules and items mentioned in the preceding Article.
Primary schools and educational institutions shall, for new enrollees that have not received immunization by schedule, prepare name lists and notify local competent health authorities to request for dispatching personnel to assist in the make-up immunization, and when necessary, coordinate with local education or social affairs competent authorities for cooperation.
Procedures for the notification and operation of the preceding Paragraph are as follows:
1. notifying legal proxy in writing results of examination and matters concerning make-up immunization;
2. for children not completing immunization for other special medical reasons, local medical care institutions shall be coordinated or children referred to for further examination to decide if make-up immunization should be conducted;
3. assisting local competent health authorities to implement matters concerning immunization or make-up immunization and to follow-up children to complete immunization;
4. coordinating local competent health authorities in recording and providing them with electronic databases on various immunizations for the period the students are in schools.
